  • Method Details

    • deleteChangesets

      public ManageChangesetsApi.DeleteChangesetsAdapter deleteChangesets(String hrn, String layerId, Optional<String> version)
      Deletes one or more changesets where the version number can be specified by the query parameter 'version', where the value must be an integer, bigger than 0 and the comparator should be one of the below list: - < - =lt= Example: To remove changesets older than version number 10, a DELETE /layers/{layerId}/changesets?version=lt=10 could be executed. The service will begin the process to remove the versions from version 9 until the version 0. During the deletion process, newer versions can be created and won't be affected.

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/changesets

      Method: DELETE

      Expected answers:

      code 204 : String (An empty response as a result of a user-request with accepted MIME type application/x-empty.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      code 401 : Error (Unauthorized to perform the request.)

      code 403 : Error (Forbidden request. Insufficient rights to perform the request.)

      code 404 : Error (Not found.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The unique identifier of the layer.
      version - The query parameter used to specify the versions to be deleted. The value must be an integer, bigger than 1, and the comparator should be one of the below list: - < - =lt=

    • getChangeset

      public ManageChangesetsApi.GetChangesetAdapter getChangeset(String hrn, String layerId, String version, Optional<String> pageToken, Optional<Integer> limit)
      Retrieves one Changeset from the layer by version. Each successful write transaction to the layer is stored as one single Changeset, which can contain modifications applied to one or more features. The response payload may be split in multiple pages, next page is written in the property 'nextPageToken', which then, can be retrieved by using the 'pageToken' parameter.

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/changesets/{version}

      Method: GET

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : Changeset (One Changeset which contains FeatureCollections grouped by operation.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      code 400 : Error (Malformed or Bad Request.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      code 401 : Error (Unauthorized to perform the request.)

      code 403 : Error (Forbidden request. Insufficient rights to perform the request.)

      code 404 : Error (Not found.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      code 513 : Error (Response payload too large.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The unique identifier of the layer.
      version - The version of a Changeset.
      pageToken - The page token where the iteration will continue.
      limit - The maximum number of features in the response. Default is _30000_. Hard limit is _100000_.

    • getChangesets

      public ManageChangesetsApi.GetChangesetsAdapter getChangesets(String hrn, String layerId, Optional<Integer> startVersion, Optional<Integer> endVersion, Optional<String> pageToken, Optional<Integer> limit)
      Retrieves the existing Changesets from the layer. Each successful write transaction to the layer is stored as one single Changeset, which can contain modifications applied to one or more features. The response payload may be split in multiple pages, next page is written in the property 'nextPageToken', which then, can be retrieved by using the 'pageToken' parameter.

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/changesets

      Method: GET

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : ChangesetCollection (A collection of Changesets which contains FeatureCollections grouped by operation.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      code 400 : Error (Malformed or Bad Request.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      code 401 : Error (Unauthorized to perform the request.)

      code 403 : Error (Forbidden request. Insufficient rights to perform the request.)

      code 404 : Error (Not found.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      code 513 : Error (Response payload too large.) Headers : X-Correlation-ID - X-Request-ID -

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The unique identifier of the layer.
      startVersion - Define start of version-range [version >= startVersion].
      endVersion - Define end of version-range [version <= endVersion].
      pageToken - The page token where the iteration will continue.
      limit - The maximum number of features in the response. Default is _30000_. Hard limit is _100000_.
